data.chText: （尤指宗教节假日的）前夜，前夕
data.enText: the day or evening before an event, especially a religious festival or holiday
a New Year's Eve party (= on 31 December)
on the eve of the election

example: he always arrives on the eve of her departure

tr: the latter part of the day (the period of decreasing daylight from late afternoon until nightfall)
example: he enjoyed the evening light across the lake
on the eve of the French Revolution

value.def: The eve of a particular event or occasion is the day before it, or the period of time just before it.
value.tran: 前夕;前一天；前一段时间

trans: 圣诞夜；圣诞前夜；平安夜；圣诞前夕；圣诞节前夕
新年前夕；除夕；除夕夜；新年除夕；缘满除夕夜
